 More precisely.

28:30.320 --> 28:39.080
 Can ask you for an impossible task, which is try to summarize the book so far, maybe

28:39.080 --> 28:41.760
 by giving a little examples.

28:41.760 --> 28:47.000
 Also from the sorting and the search and the combinatorial algorithms, if you were to give

28:47.000 --> 28:56.240
 a summary, a quick elevator summary, depending how many floors there are in the building.

28:56.240 --> 29:05.480
 The first volume called fundamental algorithms talks about something that you can't do without.

29:05.480 --> 29:13.160
 You have to know the basic concepts of what is a program, what is an algorithm.

29:13.160 --> 29:18.200
 And it also talks about a low level machine so you can have some kind of an idea of what's

29:18.200 --> 29:20.560
 going on.

29:20.560 --> 29:27.080
 And it has basic concepts of input and output and subroutines.

29:27.080 --> 29:28.080
 Induction.

29:28.080 --> 29:37.080
 Mathematical preliminary, so the thing that makes my book different from a lot of others

29:37.080 --> 29:44.080
 is that I try to not only present the algorithm, but I try to analyze them, which means quantitatively

29:44.080 --> 29:48.280
 I say not only does it work, but it works this fast.

29:48.280 --> 29:49.800
 And so I need math for that.

29:49.800 --> 29:56.320
 And then the standard way to structure data inside and represent information in the computer.

29:56.320 --> 29:58.720
 So that's all volume one.

29:58.720 --> 30:04.320
 Volume two talks, it's called semi numerical algorithms, and here we're writing programs,

30:04.320 --> 30:07.760
 but we're also dealing with numbers.

30:07.760 --> 30:14.120
 Algorithms deal with any kinds of objects, but when there's objects or numbers, well,

30:14.120 --> 30:20.760
 then we have certain special paradigms that apply to things that have numbers.

30:20.760 --> 30:27.600
 And so there's arithmetic on numbers, and there's matrices full of numbers, there's

30:27.600 --> 30:33.760
 random numbers, and there's power series full of numbers, there's different algebraic

30:33.760 --> 30:37.360
 concepts that have numbers in structured ways.

30:37.360 --> 30:42.000
 And arithmetic in the way a computer would think about arithmetic, so floating point.

30:42.000 --> 30:46.560
 Floating point arithmetic, high precision arithmetic, not only addition, subtraction,

30:46.560 --> 30:51.040
 multiplication, but also comparison of numbers.

